---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Downloads — Tempo"
  description="Everything you can download for Tempo — the app itself, scores, and utilities."
>
  <header class="page-header">
    <nav class="page-nav">
      <a href="/">← Tempo</a>
    </nav>
    <h1>Downloads</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      Tempo is the app, but it's not the whole story. Scores teach Tempo about
      your sources; utilities fit alongside Tempo to fill workflow gaps. Pick
      what you need.
    </p>
  </header>

  <main class="cards">

    <article class="card">
      <h2>Tempo</h2>
      <p class="card-desc">
        A native macOS event hub. Aggregates events from every source in your
        homelab — Kopia, UniFi, Home Assistant, Uptime Kuma, Proxmox, GitHub
        Actions, your Calendar — into a single chronological timeline, with
        action buttons that actually do something.
      </p>
      <p class="card-meta">
        macOS 15+ · Signed + notarized DMG · No App Store
      </p>
      <p class="card-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="https://tempoapp.app/Tempo.dmg">Download DMG</a>
        <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/blog/">Read the blog</a>
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h2>Scores</h2>
      <p class="card-desc">
        Small declarative JSON files that teach Tempo about a source — the
        color, the severity rules, and the one-click actions to attach. Drop
        one in, the source is wired up.
      </p>
      <p class="card-meta">
        Tempo ships with a core set bundled in. The catalog below adds
        downloadable extras for tools the bundle doesn't cover.
      </p>
      <p class="card-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/scores/">Browse the catalog</a>
        <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="https://github.com/caereforge/tempo-scores">Source on GitHub</a>
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h2>Utilities</h2>
      <p class="card-desc">
        Shortcuts, scripts, and small helper tools that complement Tempo. They
        don't define a Tempo source — they fit alongside, filling the workflow
        gaps that the app itself doesn't try to solve.
      </p>
      <p class="card-meta">
        First entry: a macOS Shortcut to copy <code>message://</code> deep
        links from Apple Mail. More land as the catalog grows.
      </p>
      <p class="card-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="https://github.com/caereforge/tempo-utilities">Browse on GitHub</a>
      </p>
    </article>

  </main>

  <footer class="page-footer">
    <p>
      Looking for documentation? See the <a href="/blog/">blog</a> for design
      notes, dev logs, and walkthroughs.
    </p>
  </footer>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-header {
    max-width: var(--measure);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2rem 1.25rem 1.5rem;
  }
  .page-nav {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .page-nav a { color: var(--text2); }
  .page-nav a:hover { color: var(--text); }

  .page-header h1 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .lede {
    color: var(--text2);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    max-width: 60ch;
  }

  .cards {
    max-width: var(--measure);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem 4rem;
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .card {
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 1.5rem 1.25rem;
    background: var(--bg-elev, transparent);
  }

  .card h2 {
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem 0;
  }

  .card-desc {
    color: var(--text2);
    max-width: 60ch;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .card-meta {
    color: var(--text3);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    max-width: 60ch;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .card-meta code {
    background: var(--bg-elev, rgba(0,0,0,0.05));
    padding: 0.1rem 0.3rem;
    border-radius: 3px;
    font-size: 0.85em;
  }

  .card-actions {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }

  .btn {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.5rem 0.9rem;
    border-radius: 6px;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    transition: background 0.15s, color 0.15s, border-color 0.15s;
  }

  .btn-primary {
    background: var(--blue);
    color: var(--bg);
  }
  .btn-primary:hover {
    background: var(--blue-hover, var(--blue));
    filter: brightness(1.05);
  }

  .btn-secondary {
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    color: var(--text2);
    background: transparent;
  }
  .btn-secondary:hover {
    color: var(--text);
    border-color: var(--text2);
  }

  .page-footer {
    max-width: var(--measure);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 1.25rem 4rem;
    color: var(--text3);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }
  .page-footer a { color: var(--blue); }
</style>
